Her Washington Post obit:
&quot; KATHERINE FLOYD-JONES SHERMAN Club Member Katherine Floyd-Jones Sherman, 99, a member of the Sulgrave Club and the Colonial Dames, died Dec. 7 at the Washington Home. She had Alzheimer's disease. Mrs. Sherman, a resident of Washington since the late 1960s, was born in Helena, Mont. She grew up in St. Louis and in Europe, where she attended schools in Italy, Austria, France and Belgium. In 1922, she married Hoyt Sherman, who became president of an oil company in Venezuela in the mid-1920s. They lived in Venezuela until he retired in the mid-1950s. They moved to Winter Park, Fla., where Mr. Sherman died in 1962. Mrs. Sherman's survivors include three children, Mary-Hoyt Sherman Joyce of Washington, Katherine Sherman Lodge of Nantucket, Mass., and John Sherman of London; a sister, Mrs. George Everitt of Newport, R.I., and six grandchildren. &quot;
